The '''Vanikoro monarch''' ('''''Mayrornis schistaceus''''') is a species of bird in the [[Monarch flycatcher|monarch]] family [[Endemism|endemic]] to the [[Santa Cruz Islands]]. Its natural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests and it is threatened by [[habitat loss]]. Alternate names for the Vanikoro monarch include '''slaty flycatcher''' (an alternate name shared with the [[Slaty monarch]]), '''small slaty flycatcher''', '''small slaty monarch''' and the '''Vanikoro flycatcher''' (not be confused with the species of the same name, ''[[Myiagra vanikorensis]]'').

